    {
      "id": "82f4e129-9928-4cb4-8f2c-134b511c3694_436f443d-d9ef-4289-afb9-8029b45c7929",
      "label": "Describe something you built from scratch. Go five levels deep — what it was, why you built it, what the architecture looked like, what broke, and what you'd do differently.",
      "type": "textarea",
      "required": true,
      "value": "I'm excited about the opportunity to work at Clipboard because I'm drawn to organizations that operate at scale, solve complex technical challenges, and prioritize innovation and long-term impact. Throughout my experience at Microsoft and Amazon Robotics, I've enjoyed working at the intersection of technology, operations, and strategy — leading cross-functional initiatives, building scalable systems, and driving measurable business outcomes.\n\nWhat particularly interests me about Clipboard is the opportunity to contribute to high-impact products and programs while collaborating with talented teams across engineering, product, and business functions. I'm especially motivated by environments where I can combine technical depth with program leadership to improve reliability, automation, and operational efficiency.\n\nIn my current role, I've led large-scale resilience and automation initiatives, developed AI-driven workflow solutions, and managed complex cross-organizational programs under executive visibility. I enjoy taking ambiguous problems, creating structure, and driving execution from concept through delivery. I'd be excited to bring that same mindset to Clipboard while continuing to grow in a fast-paced and innovative environment.\n\nBeyond the technical challenges, I'm also looking for a company whose culture emphasizes ownership, collaboration, and continuous improvement. From what I've seen, Clipboard aligns strongly with those values, which makes the opportunity especially compelling to me.",
      "source": "why-company-template.md (substituted [Company]='Clipboard')",
      "status": "filled",
      "matched_rule": "why_company_essay",
      "options": null,
      "_ashby_type": "LongText",
